  "texts": [
    "Data augmentation techniques such as random horizontal flips, rotations (±15°), and zooms (0.8-1.2x) are applied to improve model generalization.",
    "B. Textual Feature EncodingThe text encoder processes Bangla disaster-related text using transformer-based models (BanglaBERT, mBERT, XLM-RoBERTa) following an effective approach to low-resource language understanding.",
    "Tokenization and Embedding: All sentences are tokenized into sub-words based on WordPiece tokenization, handling out-of-vocabulary words characteristic of social media content.",
    "Tokens are embedded using positional encodings:P E(pos, 2i) = sin pos 10000 2i/d model(1)P E(pos, 2i + 1) = cospos 10000 2i/d model (2)where pos is the position, i is the dimension index, and d model is the embedding dimension.",
    "Feature Extraction: Contextual representations are produced by multi-head selfattention mechanisms:Attention(Q, K, V) = softmax QK T √ d k V(3)where Q, K, V represent query, key, and value matrices, and d k is the key dimension."
